Evidence of ventricular preexcitation, complete left bundle branch block, right bundle branch block (RBBB), or incomplete RBBB.
With a resting heart rate outside the range of 45 to 100 bpm.
Abnormalities on physical examination, vital signs, ECG, or clinical laboratory values, unless those abnormalities were judged clinically insignificant by the investigator.
Refusal to abstain from caffeine or xanthine containing beverages entirely during confinement.

description.full: Refusal to abstain from food 10 hours preceding and 4 hours following study drug administration and to abstain from caffeine or xanthine containing beverages entirely during each confinement.
Positive urine cotinine results or frequent (> 1x per week) smoking or use of nicotine products within 45 days of study drug administration..
Blood or blood products donated within 30 days prior to study drug administration or through the end-of-study visit, except as required by this protocol.
description.brief: Blood or blood products donated within 30 days

Subjects who will not allow hair to be removed at the proposed patch application sites which may prevent proper placement of the patch.
Subjects for whom a proper assessment of possible application site reactions would be confounded by local skin conditions.
